        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:3:35:1",
        "text": [
          " مَنْ حَفَرَ لِمَيِّتٍ قَبْراً كَانَ كَمَنْ بَوَّأَهُ بَيْتاً مُوَافِقاً إِلَى يَوْمِ الْقِيَامَةِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Sayf Bin Umeyra, from Sa’ad Bin Tareyf, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who digs a grave for a deceased would be like the one provides a compatible house up to the Day of Judgement’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. Ali has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Sayf ibn ‘ Amira from Sa‘d ibn Tarif who has said the following: “Abu Ja’far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One who prepares the grave for a believing person is like one who provides him a desirable dwelling up to the Day of Judgment.”’ "
          ]
        }
      }
